{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the \u00a3100k childcare income cap in line with inflation",
        "additional_details": "The \u00a3100,000 cap has been frozen since the 30-hours childcare scheme began in 2017. Since then, CPI inflation has risen by around 35%, meaning \u00a3100,000 now has the real-terms value of roughly \u00a3135,000. Earnings have increased while the cap has not, pulling more families over the limit each year. The per-parent cliff edge also produces unfair outcomes between households with similar or lower total incomes.",
        "background": "Increase the \u00a3100,000 per-parent childcare eligibility income cap to restore its original real-terms value, and automatically uprate it each year in line with inflation to prevent further fiscal drag and unfair loss of childcare support.",
